node.text:
I remember my first visit to Europe with my parents when I was around 15 yrs old, and remember liking the food where we were, in Italy, but saying when I got home, I was going to have a Club Sandwich. (I wasn’t a huge Club Sandwich fan or anything, but perhaps it was just something simple and familiar to me.) A lot has changed since then, and a lot of time has passed, and Club Sandwiches have gone international*, including this terrific, non-traditional one I had for lunch with @latuilealoup at @caluche_cafe_cave where the owner kindly offered to translate the menu for me when he heard my accent. (Some people get irked by that, but I find it charming. But I did ask him how to translate “Club Sandwich” in French😄) Anyhow this one was excellent and featured homemade pastrami. It seemed huge when they brought it out, but somehow I managed to eat the whole thing🤷🏼However I did have to pass on dessert…
.
#paris #restaurant #sandwich #clubsandwich #pastrami
.
*in keeping with local customs, though, I did eat it with a knife and fork😅🍽

node.text:
It was so much fun hanging out all afternoon with the lovely Amy and Jean Pasquet @cognacpasquet where we wandered through their lush grapevine and toured their cellar, with old oak barrels sitting Cognac and Pineau des Charentes, before ending up here, in the tasting room. (I got a few sips of their new raspberry apéritif made from berries behind their family distillery and…wow💥was that good…) Their organic Pineau de Charentes is modern-tasting with vibrant, bright grape flavors with a lush background of young Cognac, especially the dark red rosé, and I was thrilled to meet them! (And am looking forward to making Jean’s mother’s Galette Charentaise, a recipe for buttery shortbread from the region, that Amy slipped me…😉)
.
#cognacpasquat #cognac #pineaudescharentes #galette #charentes
